A meeting of the National Security Council presided by President Muhammadu Buhari, is underway on Wednesday, at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The meeting, being held behind closed doors in the Council Chamber, is expected to review the current security situation in Nigeria, especially before the general election. It is coming after the launch of security equipment donated by the Coalition Against Covid-19 (CACOVID) at the Council Chambers. The National Security Council advises the president on public security issues among others. Details later. 